      • initialTimeout

        public B initialTimeout(int initialTimeout)
        Sets the timeout for the initial RPC, in milliseconds. Subsequent calls will use this value adjusted according to timeoutMultiplier(double). Default value is 20000.
        Returns:
        the builder
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the provided timeout is < 0

      • timeoutMultiplier

        public B timeoutMultiplier(double timeoutMultiplier)
        Sets the timeout multiplier. This value is used to compute the timeout for a retried RPC. Timeout is computed as timeoutMultiplier * previousTimeout. Default value is 1.5.
        Returns:
        the builder
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the provided timeout multiplier is < 0

      • maxTimeout

        public B maxTimeout(int maxTimeout)
        Sets the maximum timeout for a RPC call, in milliseconds. Default value is 100000. If maxTimeout is lower than the initial timeout the initialTimeout(int) value is used instead.
        Returns:
        the builder
